  "text": "See Ref. [CITATION_1] were we demonstrate viscoelastic instabilitites under steady electro-osmotic pumping and discuss our device in more detail. Briefly, the experimental details are as follows: a microfluidic toolkit (µTK) from MicraLyne Inc. Polymer solutions were made by adding high molecular weight (18 × 10 6 Da) polyacrylamide from Polysciences Inc. to a 20:80 vol.% methanol:water mixture; methanol is used to prevent aging during storage [25] . The overlap concentration c * is ≈ 300 ppm, and we work in the dilute regime (c < c * ).",
